<item>
            <title>[LDAP-226] empty OrFilter should be false (|) and empty AndFilter should be true (&amp;), see also rfc4526</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/LDAP-226</link>
                <project id="10071" key="LDAP">Spring LDAP</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;rfc4526 makes it clear that (|) is false and (&amp;amp;) is true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;currently an empty OrFilter() is &quot;&quot;, same for empty AndFilter().&lt;br/&gt;
this is logically wrong.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;rationale:&lt;br/&gt;
AndFilter(&quot;foo=bar&quot;, OrFilter(&quot;uid=u1&quot;, &quot;uid=u2&quot;))&lt;br/&gt;
gives (&amp;amp;(foo=bar)(|(uid=u1)(uid=u2)))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AndFilter(&quot;foo=bar&quot;, OrFilter(&quot;uid=u1&quot;))&lt;br/&gt;
gives (&amp;amp;(foo=bar)(uid=u1))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AndFilter(&quot;foo=bar&quot;, OrFilter())&lt;br/&gt;
gives (&amp;amp;(foo=bar))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so reducing the number of &quot;or&quot;s gives more results!?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
